LONG LOVE LETTER/ Band Appreciation Post: first off thank you to the fans/supporters/followers/team members/fellow musicians! There is no us without you.
PHOTOS BY @cashonlyemmett

 Secondly, to the precious handsome rock and roll daddies (AKA- THE MA'AT'S) you complete me. The heartbeat to my pop and lock 😆 The amount of time and energy you've put into your craft IS manifesting into something so beautiful for all of us. I am honored to have you represent me on stage. And to have my art be brought to life through your eyes and ears and hands is like watching a master painter create a portrait of my lifetime. The way you all embellish eachother prove that we're meant to be. To be in unison with you guys is heavenly ❤️ We are making music babies, guys. Lets fall more in love with the process! I'm obsessed 🤣 ily so much @shreddy_van.halen (thank you for showing me I was meant to do this when we were kids, ill never forget this gift. TO be here 10 years later IS AMAZING)if we were a house, you'd be the walls. Thank you @xlsweater for being the brother band to Mikki Ma'at. Sharing the team with me means so much. @casualdasual Elijah, your emotional support and willpower and silent strength hold us all up, whether you feel it or not. You're the most solid melody and your singing voice crashes into all of us like a tsunami. Thank you for being the roof. Sing and yell as much as you want here ❤️ @cashonlysound Greg you've been here for least amount of time and have applied a layer of professionalism that inspires me. Thank you for stepping up to the plate sonically and business wise. I legitimately loved you as an addition INSTANTLY. The pillars to our house! @partyshev our favorite drummer in the world, our foundation.❤️ 💕 thank you for being just as weird as me and having very long death metal tangents.Thank you for being an Aquarius that literally marches to his own beat. You continue to show us how hard working can pay off if you're diligent. All of you inspire me. 
And to myself... look at what is around you. Accept the beauty. Take in as much as you give out. ✨️- Mikki Ma'at

For the geology/metaphysic nerds: Apophyllite is so cool because its a zeolite! Zeolites are complex metamorphic rocks that literally suck in metal ions and positive ions (which are concluded to be harmful to our vibrations). So they vacuum negative energy through their teeny tiny pores! Zeolites are also cool because they're helping scientists replace harmful chemicals in our detergents and in our environment! They grow in these little 4 sided pyramid shapes (tetragonal dipyramid) and that seems to POINT the energy right out! I have always been fascinated with this stone because it has such a high and fast frequency it can be heard by sensitives from simply holding it up to your ear! I hope you enjoyed learning about Apophyllite! If you want to know more about a specific specimen; comment below!

At the heart of Mikki’s music lies a fusion of various genres, including indie folk, ambient pop, and electronic elements. Mikki's voice dances effortlessly over layers of celestial synths, delicate acoustic guitar arpeggios, and subtle electronic beats, creating a balance between the earthly and the cosmic.🌸

Their lyrics often explore themes of self-discovery, human connection, and the interconnectedness of all things. Mikki’s poetic songwriting invites listeners to reflect on the profound beauty that can be found in both the ordinary and the extraordinary moments of life. Whether singing about the constellations above or the flowers in a meadow, Mikki's lyrics carry a sense of introspection that resonates deeply with their audience.🌿

 
Mark your calendars for August 20th, gather your friends, and prepare for an unforgettable celebration of joy, creativity, and reconnecting with your inner child.  You'll meet amazing performers, indulge in delicious treats, and immerse yourself in a world of wonder and play. 🐞
 
#UnleashYourInnerChild #NatureAndMusicMagic
